From: H618 video enablement <noreply@local>
Date: Tue, 17 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] media: cedrus: drop tiled NV12_32L32 output so linear NV12 is used

The DE33 (H616/H618) display-engine VI plane can only scan out LINEAR
framebuffers (no Allwinner-tiled support in the mixer; only the old DE1
frontend could detile). ffmpeg/gstreamer v4l2request prefer the tiled
NV12_32L32 capture format, which then fails to commit on the linear-only
overlay plane. Cedrus already supports linear output (UNTILED capability),
so remove the tiled format from the capture list to force linear NV12 and
enable true zero-copy direct-to-plane video.

Signed-off-by: H618 video enablement <noreply@local>
---
 drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus_video.c | 4 ----
 1 file changed, 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus_video.c b/drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus_video.c
--- a/drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus_video.c
+++ b/drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus_video.c
@@ -75,10 +75,6 @@
 		.pixelformat	= V4L2_PIX_FMT_NV12,
 		.directions	= CEDRUS_DECODE_DST,
 		.capabilities	= CEDRUS_CAPABILITY_UNTILED,
 	},
-	{
-		.pixelformat	= V4L2_PIX_FMT_NV12_32L32,
-		.directions	= CEDRUS_DECODE_DST,
-	},
 	{
 		.pixelformat	= V4L2_PIX_FMT_NV21,
 		.directions	= CEDRUS_DECODE_DST,
